  "observation": "Brainstorm triggered by plateau. 4 proposals generated.",
  "suggestion": "The system has converged on a high-fitness local optimum within fixed constraints: static morphology, static environment, static beauty definition. Parameter tuning can no longer escape. The plateau reveals that beauty itself may be too narrowly specified — it rewards polish within the current morphotype space, not novelty. Structural breaks require either (1) new degrees of freedom (temporal differentiation), (2) shifting selection pressure (seasonal cycles), or (3) new fitness surfaces (collective beauty). All three share a principle: make the fitness landscape non-stationary or expand the action space. Plateau = proof the current architecture is saturated.; [medium] Temporal cell differentiation — enable organisms to express different cell types at different life stages. Add lifecycle phases (juvenile/adult/senescent) where gene expression rules change. Cells have conditional 'activateAfter' properties keyed to age or energy thresholds. — Current morphospace exhausted: organisms have converged on static body plans. Temporal differentiation opens new strategy space — evolve protective shells that dissolve for reproduction, growth that accelerates then halts, beauty patterns that emerge only at reproductive peak. Fundamentally changes what 'optimal' looks like.; [easy] Environmental oscillation — introduce seasonal cycles. World resources (light, nutrients) shift periodically on a 20-30 cycle rhythm. Survival pressure, beauty reward, and efficiency payoff change with season. Organisms cannot optimize for one static state. — Static equilibrium reached. Seasonal pressure prevents any solution from being 'final' — organisms that thrive in summer fail in winter, forcing evolution of flexibility and trade-off strategies. Dynamic selection landscape keeps opening new niches. Beauty now rewards seasonally-adapted forms (e.g., iridescence that works in both high and low light).; [hard] Quorum-based collective beauty scoring — modify beauty evaluation to reward group patterns, not just individual morphology. Organisms within distance < 3 units form implicit colonies; beauty score includes spatial harmony (symmetry, color complementarity, density patterns of the group). Fitness contribution: 0.15 of composite score now depends on neighbor form. — Unlocks cooperative evolution. Current system optimizes solitary forms; collective beauty opens morphological space (fractals, emergent patterns, division-of-labor). Enables evolutionary strategies that require multiple organisms (camouflage clusters, display swarms). Shifts beauty from 'individual perfection' to 'relational harmony' — completely new aesthetic dimension.",
